file=Engineering/dev/custom/architecture-decisions/assets/adr-template.md · a[t:ADR-[NNN]: [short title of the decision]=**Status:** [proposed / accepted / superseded-by ADR-NNN] \· **Date:** [YYYY-MM-DD] \· **Deciders:** [dev + domain agents/operator] \· **Supersedes:** [ADR-NNN or —]\n · c:Context=[The forces at play, honestly. What problem, what constraints (the stack profile, the Security Charter, budget, timeline), what's pushing us. State the assumptions.]\n · oc:Options considered=[At least two. For each: what it is, and its trade-offs. "We only found one option" is itself worth recording.]\n\n1. **[Option A]** — [pros / cons]\n2. **[Option B]** — [pros / cons]\n3. **[Option C]** (if any) — [pros / cons]\n · d:Decision=[The option chosen, and the deciding reason. One paragraph.]\n · c:Consequences=- **Positive:** [what this buys us]\n- **Negative / costs:** [what we accept — the downsides, stated plainly]\n- **Follow-ups:** [migrations, ADRs this forces later, risks to watch]\n · dr:Domain review=[Which agents reviewed (data/backend/frontend/mobile/security/reliability), and any dissent — recorded, not hidden.]\n · cc:Charter check=[Confirm this decision does not weaken any Security Charter rail. If it touches security posture, aegis reviewed.]\n